overall_summary: Discord discussion centered on the upcoming AI16Z → ElizaOS token migration (portal-based, starting Nov 7 with a 90-day window) and associated tokenomics changes. In parallel, partners/core-dev conversations highlighted near-term product work (Eliza Cloud for Devconnect, x402 gateway, Farcaster miniapps) and surfaced security concerns (malicious x402 resource server code and scam activity).
key_facts: AI16Z token migration to ElizaOS is scheduled to start on 2025-11-07 and will run for at least 90 days.
The stated swap ratio is 1 AI16Z token to 6 ElizaOS tokens (equivalently, 0.1666 AI16Z for 1 ElizaOS).
Total token supply is planned to increase from 6.6B to 11B tokens, and circulating supply is planned to increase from 6.6B to 7.4B at migration start.
The post-migration token allocation discussed is 75% community, 15% SAFT, and 10% team/contributors.
Migration is described as portal-based and manual for self-custody/on-chain holders (not snapshot-based).
Binance and Gate.io were cited as exchanges expected to support automatic migration for exchange-held balances.
No lock-up period for migrated tokens was stated for holders.
An Eliza Cloud release is being prepared for a demonstration at Devconnect.
The team reported work on an x402 gateway that integrates with DegenAI.
Some x402 resource servers were reported to contain malicious code that needs fixing.

overall_focus.claim: No GitHub activity was reported for elizaOS/eliza on 2025-11-01 (0 new PRs, 0 merged PRs, 0 new issues, 0 active contributors).

Recent (late Oct) development focus included a unified messaging API, a Jobs API for stateless agent interactions, payment middleware, PostgreSQL Row-Level Security for multi-tenancy, health check endpoints, and CLI cloud authentication.

discord_updates.summary: Users asked how the AI16Z → ElizaOS migration will work; moderators reiterated that migration starts Nov 7, runs 90 days, and uses a migration portal (manual for self-custody). Tokenomics and supply/circulating changes were repeatedly clarified, along with the note that exchanges may or may not provide automatic migration support.

A developer asked for a cleaner pattern to suppress Bootstrap/LLM responses for custom slash commands, describing a current patch-based approach in the Telegram plugin. The channel also contained side discussion on Counterparty assets (Rare Pepes / Fake Rares, PEPEPIZZA) and a scam report involving a suspicious file that led to a ban.

Partners discussed shipping an Eliza Cloud release for a Devconnect demo, building an x402 gateway that takes DegenAI, and researching on-chain cloud integration with the Ethereum Foundation around ERC-8004. They also discussed using x402.elizaos.ai as a central API hub and noted an Otaku Farcaster miniapp dependent on Coinbase integration (targeted for the following week).
A brief note flagged that some x402 resource servers contain malicious code that needs fixing; limited additional technical detail was provided in the captured excerpt.

user_feedback.feedback_summary: UI/UX feedback reported usability limitations when providing LP to Aerodrome and requested larger windows plus clearer chain distinctions and sorting/filtering by chain in Tokens/History views.

strategic_insights.theme: Migration execution risk concentrated in portal UX, comms, and exchange support variance
strategic_insights.insight: Repeated user questions focused on whether exchanges and self-custody wallets will migrate automatically, implying the portal workflow and exchange-by-exchange handling will be the primary operational load during the migration window.
implications_or_questions: Is the migration portal UX and documentation ready for high-volume self-custody users on day one?
Is there a maintained list of exchanges confirmed to auto-migrate vs requiring manual action?

strategic_insights.theme: Security posture during migration and x402 ecosystem maintenance
strategic_insights.insight: Moderation actions against scam behavior and a report of malicious code in some x402 resource servers surfaced alongside migration comms, indicating two concurrent security-sensitive surfaces: user phishing/scams and third-party/server code hygiene.
implications_or_questions: Is there a public checklist for verifying the official migration portal link and warning users about impersonation?
Is there an audit/remediation plan for x402 resource servers flagged as malicious?

market_analysis.observation: Tokenomics and supply/circulating changes (6.6B → 11B supply; 6.6B → 7.4B circulating) were a major focus of community discussion during migration planning.
market_analysis.relevance: These parameters define holder conversion expectations and are central to external messaging, exchange coordination, and liquidity planning.

market_analysis.observation: Discussion included Protocol Owned Liquidity planning referenced as 275M tokens.
market_analysis.relevance: POL sizing can affect liquidity provisioning strategy and post-migration market structure.
